title: GOLF: Waterloo caps stellar regular season
text:
GOLF: Waterloo caps stellar regular season Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
WATERLOO — The Waterloo golf team wrapped up the 2015 regular season with a performance that mirrored many of its outcomes this year. 
The Indians, who have shot no higher than 221 this season, posted a 210 to defeat Penn Yan Academy 210-223 Thursday at Silver Creek Golf Club. 
Waterloo (14-1, 12-0) completed another unbeaten Finger Lakes East campaign — it was 11-0-1 last year. 
“We were hoping for [another unbeaten season]. Another goal was to improve our scores, and in some games we did that,” Waterloo coach Joe Sposato said. “One big thing for us this year were players like Brandon Valder and Chance Sheldon, who really did a good job in their first seasons on varsity.” 
Waterloo’s Hunter Sheldon registered three birdies Thursday to highlight a 1-over-par 36. Kyle Bailey fired a 42. 
“One of the biggest things going for us was that we could get outstanding scores from anybody,” Sposato added. 
Bryce Johnson and Andrew Christensen carded 41s for Penn Yan (6-6, 6-5). 
Wayne 239, Midlakes incomplete 
Pal-Mac 250, Midlakes incomplete 
HOPEWELL — John Sweeney shot a 4-over 40 for Wayne (9-4, 7-4) at Clifton Springs Country Club. 
Nick Smith chalked up a 42 for Midlakes (1-10). Sumner Tessier notched a 43 for Pal-Mac (3-8). 
FINGER LAKES WEST 
South Seneca 242, Naples 261 
OVID — Max Stamberger and Kyle Shields posted 11-over 47s for South Seneca (3-7, 3-6) at Bonavista State Golf Course. 
Andrew Fleischman signed for a 38 to lead the Big Green (3-7, 3-6).
